# Webview dev hot reload (do not run full compile every edit)

## Daily UI work (`src/webview/**`)

When the user (or agent) iterates on Bitstream / Sensor Telemetry / Sensor Studio **webview** code:

1. Assume **`npm run dev:webview`** (or **`npm run dev`**) is running — **Vite HMR** applies saves in seconds.
2. **Do not** run **`npm run compile`** after every webview-only change.
3. Use **IDE TypeScript diagnostics** or a targeted check when unsure.

## Bridge / broker (`start:bridge`)

- **`npm run start:bridge`** — one-shot; restart manually after **`src/serialport-bridge/**`**, **`src/combined-bridge-entry.ts`**, or **`src/bitstream2/**`** bridge-side edits.
- **`npm run start:bridge:watch`** — auto-restarts bridge on those files (use when editing bridge code frequently).

## When **`npm run compile`** is required

- Before **`npm run package`** / VSIX install
- After **`src/extension.ts`** or other **extension host** entry changes (unless **`watch:all`** is already running)
- End-of-feature / CI gate when the user asks for a full build verify

## Typical two-terminal flow

```bash
npm run start:bridge          # or start:bridge:watch
npm run dev:webview           # http://localhost:5173/?app=bitstream
```

Hard-reload the browser tab after **`vite.config.ts`** changes or stale HMR.
